hwCBQoSClassifierIndexNext.name: hwCBQoSClassifierIndexNext
hwCBQoSClassifierIndexNext.description: The value of this object identifies the index of the next available traffic classifier. The index defined when the user creates a traffic class must be the same as the value of hwCBQoSClassifierIndexNext; otherwise, the traffic class cannot be created.

hwCBQoSClassifierCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSClassifierCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSClassifierCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Traffic Classifier configuration information.

hwCBQoSClassifierIndex.name: hwCBQoSClassifierIndex
hwCBQoSClassifierIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of the traffic classifier. The value ranges from 0 to 4096. This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSClassifierName.name: hwCBQoSClassifierName
hwCBQoSClassifierName.description: This object indicates the name of the traffic classifier. The value of this object is a string of 1 to 64 visible ASCII characters. This object has no default value. No space can exist between characters in the string. The initial space and end space are ignored.

hwCBQoSClassifierRuleCount.name: hwCBQoSClassifierRuleCount
hwCBQoSClassifierRuleCount.description: The value of this object identifies the number of the matching rules for the traffic classifier. The value ranges from 0 to 16. This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSClassifierOperator.name: hwCBQoSClassifierOperator
hwCBQoSClassifierOperator.description: The value of this object identifies the relationship between matching rules. The value of this object can be AND(1) or OR(2). The default value is OR(2).

hwCBQoSClassifierLayer.name: hwCBQoSClassifierLayer
hwCBQoSClassifierLayer.description: Configuration layer of traffic classifier. Only hardware QoS support it. -1(unavailable) is returned only when getting value from software QoS. -1(unavailable) can't be set.

hwCBQoSClassifierRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSClassifierRowStatus
hwCBQoSClassifierRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status. The value of this object can be Active(1), CreateAndGo(4), or Destroy(6). This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSMatchRuleCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSMatchRuleCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSMatchRuleCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Match Rule configuration information.

hwCBQoSMatchRuleIndex.name: hwCBQoSMatchRuleIndex
hwCBQoSMatchRuleIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the rule index. The value ranges from 0 to 15. This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSMatchRuleIfNot.name: hwCBQoSMatchRuleIfNot
hwCBQoSMatchRuleIfNot.description: The value of this object identifies the if-match rule is a Match or NotMatch statement. The value of this object can be match(1) or match-not(2).

hwCBQoSMatchRuleType.name: hwCBQoSMatchRuleType
hwCBQoSMatchRuleType.description: The value of this object identifies the rule type. The value of this object can be any of the following: any(1) ipv4-acl(2) rtp-port(3) protocol(4) ip-prec(5) dscp(6) vlan-8021p(7) mpls-exp(8) source-mac(9) destination-mac(10) classifier(11) inbound-interface(12) mac-group(13) ipv6-acl(14) qos-local-id(15) fr-de(16) atm-clp(17) ipv6-dscp(18) ipv6-next-header(19) ipv6-any(20) ipv6-dst-ip(21) ipv6-src-ip(22) rule-string(23) vlan-id(24) outbound-interface(25) l2-protocol(26) l2Acl(27), tcpFlag(28), cvlanId(29), doubleTag(30), sourceQosLocalId(31), cvlan8021p(32), discard(33), dlci(34), app-protocol(35), protocol-group(36), vlanid-cvlanid(37) This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSMatchRuleStringValue.name: hwCBQoSMatchRuleStringValue
hwCBQoSMatchRuleStringValue.description: This object indicates the rule contents. The value range and the default value of the object vary with hwCBQoSMatchRuleType. When the supported types are Source-MAC(9) and Destination-MAC(10), the value of this object can be a string of six ASCII characters, which represents a MAC address. For example, abcdef indicates the MAC address 6162-6364-6566. When the supported types are ipv6-dst-ip(21) and ipv6-src-ip(22), the value of this object is a string of 16 ASCII characters, which represents an IPv6 address. For example, 1111111111111111 indicates an IPv6 address 3131-3131-3131-3131-3131-3131-3131-3131. This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1.name: hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1
hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1.description: This object indicates the rule contents. The value range and the default value of the object vary with hwCBQoSMatchRuleType. When the supported type is ipv4-acl(2), the value of this object ranges from 2000 to 4099. When the type is ip-prec(5), the value of this object ranges from 2^1 to 2^7, respectively representing the IP precedence from 0 to 7. When the supported types are dscp(6) and ipv6-dscp(18), the value ranges from 2^1 to 2^32, respectively representing the DSCP value ranging from 32 to 63. When the type is ipv6-acl(14), the value of this object ranges from 2000 to 3999. When the type is ipv6-dscp(18), the value of this object ranges from 0 to 63. When the type is Ipv6-next-header(19), the value ranges from 0 to 255. When the type is tcp-flag(27), the value ranges from 0 to 63. When the types are ipv6-dst-ip(21) and ipv6-src-ip(22), the value ranges from 0 to 128. This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2.name: hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2
hwCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2.description: This object indicates the rule contents. The value range and the default value of the object vary with hwCBQoSMatchRuleType. When the supported type is dscp(6), the value ranges from 2^1 to 2^32, respectively representing the DSCP value ranging from 0 to 31. This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSMatchRuleRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSMatchRuleRowStatus
hwCBQoSMatchRuleRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status. The value of this object can be Active(1), CreateAndGo(4), or Destroy(6). This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSMatchMacMask.name: hwCBQoSMatchMacMask
hwCBQoSMatchMacMask.description: Value of Match Rule. Source-MAC(9): SIZE (0..6) HHHHHH for example: ffff00 means the match rule is 'if-match source-mac XX-XX-XX ff-ff-00' Destination-MAC(10): SIZE (0..6) HHHHHH for example: ffff00 means the match rule is 'if-match destination-mac XX-XX-XX ff-ff-00' default:0XFFFFFF

hwCBQoSBehaviorIndexNext.name: hwCBQoSBehaviorIndexNext
hwCBQoSBehaviorIndexNext.description: The value of this object identifies the index of the next available traffic behavior. The index used when the user creates a traffic behavior must be the same as the value of hwCBQoSBehaviorIndexNext; otherwise, the traffic behavior cannot be created.

hwCBQoSBehaviorCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSBehaviorCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSBehaviorCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Traffic Behavior configuration information.

hwCBQoSBehaviorIndex.name: hwCBQoSBehaviorIndex
hwCBQoSBehaviorIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of the traffic behavior. The value ranges from 0 to 4096. This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSBehaviorName.name: hwCBQoSBehaviorName
hwCBQoSBehaviorName.description: This object indicates the name of the traffic behavior. The value of this object is a string of 1 to 64 visible ASCII characters, with no default value. Space cannot exist between the characters in the string. The initial space and end space are ignored.

hwCBQoSBehaviorRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSBehaviorRowStatus
hwCBQoSBehaviorRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status. The value of this object can be Active(1), CreateAndGo(4), or Destroy(6). This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSCarCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSCarCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSCarCfgInfoTable.description: A table of CAR feature configuration information.

hwCBQoSCarCir.name: hwCBQoSCarCir
hwCBQoSCarCir.description: The value of this object identifies the Committed Information Rate (CIR). The value ranges from 100 to 1000000, in kbit/s, with no default value.

hwCBQoSCarCbs.name: hwCBQoSCarCbs
hwCBQoSCarCbs.description: The value of this object identifies the Committed Burst Size (CBS). The value ranges from 10000 to 33554432 bytes. The default value is 10000 bytes.

hwCBQoSCarEbs.name: hwCBQoSCarEbs
hwCBQoSCarEbs.description: Excess Burst Size. Unit: byte. 0..19375000 Only software QoS support this node. -1 is returned only when getting value from hardware QoS. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSCarPir.name: hwCBQoSCarPir
hwCBQoSCarPir.description: The value of this object identifies the Peak Information Rate (PIR). The value ranges from 100 to 1000000, in kbit/s. This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSCarPbs.name: hwCBQoSCarPbs
hwCBQoSCarPbs.description: The value of this object identifies the Peak Burst Size (PBS). The value ranges from 0 to 33554432 bytes. The default value is as follows: When hwCBQoSCarPir is not specified, the default value is 0 bytes. When hwCBQoSCarPir is specified, the default value is 10000 bytes.

hwCBQoSCarGreenAction.name: hwCBQoSCarGreenAction
hwCBQoSCarGreenAction.description: The value of this object identifies the action adopted when CIR is not reached. pass (1), discard (2), remark IP Precedence (3), remark DSCP(4), remark Mpls Exp(5), remark (6), remark 8021p(7) The default value is pass (1).

hwCBQoSCarGreenRemarkValue.name: hwCBQoSCarGreenRemarkValue
hwCBQoSCarGreenRemarkValue.description: The value is to remark When green action is remarking. the range is 11~81; the high bit represents service-class,the range is 1~8 (1:be 2:af1 3:af2 4:af3 5:af4 6:ef 7:cs6 8:cs7) the low bit represents color,the range is 1~3 (1:green 2:yellow 3:red) Only software QoS support this node. -1 is returned only when getting value from hardware QoS or when action being pass,discard of software QoS. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSCarYellowAction.name: hwCBQoSCarYellowAction
hwCBQoSCarYellowAction.description: The value of this object identifies the action adopted when CIR is exceeded but PIR is not reached. pass (1), discard (2), remark IP Precedence (3), remark DSCP(4), remark Mpls Exp(5), remark (6), remark 8021p(7) The default value is pass (1).

hwCBQoSCarYellowRemarkValue.name: hwCBQoSCarYellowRemarkValue
hwCBQoSCarYellowRemarkValue.description: The value is to remark When yellow action is remarking. For remarking DSCP, the range is 11~81; the high bit represents service-class,the range is 1~8 (1:be 2:af1 3:af2 4:af3 5:af4 6:ef 7:cs6 8:cs7) the low bit represents color,the range is 1~3 (1:green 2:yellow 3:red) For remarking IP Precedence and MPLS EXP, the range is 0~7; Only software QoS support this node. -1 is returned only when getting value from hardware QoS or when action being pass,discard of software QoS. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSCarRedAction.name: hwCBQoSCarRedAction
hwCBQoSCarRedAction.description: The value of this object identifies the action performed when PIR is exceeded. pass (1), discard (2), remark IP Precedence (3), remark DSCP(4), remark Mpls Exp(5), remark (6), remark 8021p(7) The default value is pass (1).

hwCBQoSCarRedRemarkValue.name: hwCBQoSCarRedRemarkValue
hwCBQoSCarRedRemarkValue.description: The value is to remark When red action is remarking. For remarking DSCP, the range is 11~81; the high bit represents service-class,the range is 1~8 (1:be 2:af1 3:af2 4:af3 5:af4 6:ef 7:cs6 8:cs7) the low bit represents color,the range is 1~3 (1:green 2:yellow 3:red) For remarking IP Precedence and MPLS EXP, the range is 0~7; Only software QoS support this node. -1 is returned only when getting value from hardware QoS or when action being pass,discard of software QoS. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSCarRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSCarRowStatus
hwCBQoSCarRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQosCarAggregation.name: hwCBQosCarAggregation
hwCBQosCarAggregation.description: aggregationCar(1): aggregation car; noneAggregationCar(2) : none aggregation car.

hwCBQoSGtsCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSGtsCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSGtsCfgInfoTable.description: A table of GTS feature configuration information.

hwCBQoSGtsCbs.name: hwCBQoSGtsCbs
hwCBQoSGtsCbs.description: Committed Burst Size. Unit: bit default: max(cir*1/2,15000)

hwCBQoSGtsRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSGtsRowStatus
hwCBQoSGtsRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSRemarkCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSRemarkCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSRemarkCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Remarking feature configuration information.

hwCBQoSRemarkType.name: hwCBQoSRemarkType
hwCBQoSRemarkType.description: The value of this object identifies the re-mark type. The value can be any of the following: IP-Prec(1) DSCP(2) MPLS-EXP(3) VLAN-8021p(4) ATM-CLP(5) FR-DE(6) QoS-Local-ID(7) IPV6-DSCP(8) Local-Prec(9) destination-mac(10) VLAN-ID(11) Vlan-Protocol(12) This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSRemarkValue.name: hwCBQoSRemarkValue
hwCBQoSRemarkValue.description: The value of this object identifies the re-mark value. When hwCBQoSRemarkType is ip-prec(1), mpls-exp(3), and vlan-8021p(4), the value ranges from 0 to 7. When hwCBQoSRemarkType is dscp(2) or ipv6-dscp(8), the value ranges from 0 to 63. This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSRemarkStringValue.name: hwCBQoSRemarkStringValue
hwCBQoSRemarkStringValue.description: Destination-MAC(10): SIZE (0..6) HHHHHH for example: 010102020303 means the remark action is 'remark destination-mac 0101-0202-0303'; Vlan-Protocol(12):SIZE(3..4) HEX<600-FFFF>

hwCBQoSRemarkRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSRemarkRowStatus
hwCBQoSRemarkRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status. The value of this object can be Active(1), CreateAndGo(4), or Destroy(6). This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSQueueCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSQueueCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSQueueCfgInfoTable.description: A table of queueing feature configuration information.

hwCBQoSQueueType.name: hwCBQoSQueueType
hwCBQoSQueueType.description: Queueing Type: EF: (1) AF: (2) WFQ: (3) LLQ: (4)

hwCBQoSQueueDropType.name: hwCBQoSQueueDropType
hwCBQoSQueueDropType.description: The drop type of queue. Only valid for AF and WFQ queue. -1 is returned only when getting value about EF queue. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSQueueLength.name: hwCBQoSQueueLength
hwCBQoSQueueLength.description: The length of QueueLength. Only valid for tailDrop type of AF and WFQ queue. -1 is returned only when getting value about EF queue or wred type of AF and WFQ queue. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSQueueBandwidthUnit.name: hwCBQoSQueueBandwidthUnit
hwCBQoSQueueBandwidthUnit.description: Bandwidth Unit: Absolute, Unit Kbps (1) Percent, Unit % (2) Only valid for EF and AF queue. -1 is returned only when getting value about WFQ queue. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue.name: hwCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue
hwCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue.description: Bandwidth value: Absolute value: 8~1000000. Unit: Kbps Percent value: 1~100. Only valid for EF and AF queue. -1 is returned only when getting value about WFQ queue. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSQueueCbs.name: hwCBQoSQueueCbs
hwCBQoSQueueCbs.description: Committed Burst Size. Unit: byte. Only valid for EF queue. -1 is returned only when getting value about AF or WFQ queue. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSQueueQueueNumber.name: hwCBQoSQueueQueueNumber
hwCBQoSQueueQueueNumber.description: Max number of hashed queues (a power of 2). Only valid for WFQ. -1 is returned only when getting value about AF or EF queue. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSQueueRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSQueueRowStatus
hwCBQoSQueueRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSQueueCbsRatio.name: hwCBQoSQueueCbsRatio
hwCBQoSQueueCbsRatio.description: Committed Burst Size Ratio. Unit: byte. CBS = CBS_Ratio * Bandwidth(k bps) Only valid for EF queue. -1 is returned only when getting value about AF or WFQ queue. -1 can't be set.

hwCBQoSWredCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSWredCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSWredCfgInfoTable.description: A table of WRED configuration information.

hwCBQoSWredWeightConst.name: hwCBQoSWredWeightConst
hwCBQoSWredWeightConst.description: Specify weight for calculating mean queue depth.

hwCBQoSWredDropProfileIndex.name: hwCBQoSWredDropProfileIndex
hwCBQoSWredDropProfileIndex.description: The index of wred class entry. -1 is returned when no drop profile is used. -1 can not be set.

hwCBQoSWredCfgRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSWredCfgRowStatus
hwCBQoSWredCfgRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSWredClassCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSWredClassCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSWredClassCfgInfoTable.description: A table of WRED configuration information.

hwCBQoSWredClassValue.name: hwCBQoSWredClassValue
hwCBQoSWredClassValue.description: The class value. For IP precedence based WRED, the class is IP precedence, and range is 0~7. For DSCP based WRED, the class is DSCP, and range is 0~63.

hwCBQoSWredClassLowLimit.name: hwCBQoSWredClassLowLimit
hwCBQoSWredClassLowLimit.description: The low limit of queue depth.

hwCBQoSWredClassHighLimit.name: hwCBQoSWredClassHighLimit
hwCBQoSWredClassHighLimit.description: The high limit of queue depth.

hwCBQoSNatCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSNatCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSNatCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Nat configuration information.

hwCBQoSNatRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSNatRowStatus
hwCBQoSNatRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSFirewallCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSFirewallCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSFirewallCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Firewall configuration information.

hwCBQoSFirewallAction.name: hwCBQoSFirewallAction
hwCBQoSFirewallAction.description: The value of this object identifies the firewall action. The value can be permit(1) or deny(2). The default value is permit(1).

hwCBQoSFirewallRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSFirewallRowStatus
hwCBQoSFirewallRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status. The value of this object can be Active(1), CreateAndGo(4), or Destroy(6). This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSSamplingCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSSamplingCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSSamplingCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Sampling configuration information.

hwCBQoSIfSamplingType.name: hwCBQoSIfSamplingType
hwCBQoSIfSamplingType.description: This object indicates the sampling type. The value can be any of the following: Fix-packets(1) Fix-time(2) Random-packets(3) Random-time(4) This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSSamplingNum.name: hwCBQoSSamplingNum
hwCBQoSSamplingNum.description: This object indicates the sampling parameter. The value can be any of the following: Fix-packets (1-65535) Fix-time (5-30000ms) Random-packets (1-65535) Random-time (3/6/12/24/48/96/192/383.5/767/1534/3068/6136ms) This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSSamplingRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSSamplingRowStatus
hwCBQoSSamplingRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status. The value of this object can be Active(1), CreateAndGo(4), or Destroy(6). This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSLrCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSLrCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSLrCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Line Rate configuration information.

hwCBQoSLrUnit.name: hwCBQoSLrUnit
hwCBQoSLrUnit.description: CIR Unit: Absolute, Unit bps (1) Percent, Unit % (2)

hwCBQoSLrCir.name: hwCBQoSLrCir
hwCBQoSLrCir.description: Committed Information Rate. Absolute value: 8000..155000000. Unit: bps Percent value: 1~100.

hwCBQoSLrCbs.name: hwCBQoSLrCbs
hwCBQoSLrCbs.description: Committed Burst Size. When CIR is absolute value, CBS value: 15000..155000000, default value: max(cir*1/2,15000), Unit: bit; When CIR is percent value, CBS value: 50..2000, default value: 500, Unit: ms.

hwCBQoSLrEbs.name: hwCBQoSLrEbs
hwCBQoSLrEbs.description: Excess Burst Size. When CIR is absolute value, EBS value: 0..155000000, Unit: bit; When CIR is percent value, EBS value: 0..2000, Unit: ms.

hwCBQoSLrRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSLrRowStatus
hwCBQoSLrRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSNestPolicyCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSNestPolicyCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSNestPolicyCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Hierachical Policy configuration information.

hwCBQoSNestPolicyRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSNestPolicyRowStatus
hwCBQoSNestPolicyRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSRedirectCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSRedirectCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSRedirectCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Redirect configuration information.

hwCBQoSRedirectType.name: hwCBQoSRedirectType
hwCBQoSRedirectType.description: The value of this object identifies the traffic redirection type. The value can be ip-nexthop(2), ipv6-nexthop(5), or lsppath(6). This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSRedirectIpAddress.name: hwCBQoSRedirectIpAddress
hwCBQoSRedirectIpAddress.description: This object indicates the destination address of the redirected traffic. The value of this object can be any valid IP address.This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSRedirectIfIndex.name: hwCBQoSRedirectIfIndex
hwCBQoSRedirectIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the outbound interface of the redirected traffic. This object has no value range, and the default value is 0.The outbound interface cannot be an interface of the Main Processing Unit (MPU) or a Layer 2 interface. The value 0 indicates that no outbound interface is specified.

hwCBQoSRedirectVlanId.name: hwCBQoSRedirectVlanId
hwCBQoSRedirectVlanId.description: The value of this object identifies the VLAN ID of the outbound interface of the redirected traffic.

hwCBQoSRedirectCtrlType.name: hwCBQoSRedirectCtrlType
hwCBQoSRedirectCtrlType.description: The value of this object identifies the traffic redirection control type.

hwCBQoSRedirectRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSRedirectRowStatus
hwCBQoSRedirectRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status. The value of this object can be Active(1), CreateAndGo(4), or Destroy(6). This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSRedirectLSPDstIpAddress.name: hwCBQoSRedirectLSPDstIpAddress
hwCBQoSRedirectLSPDstIpAddress.description: This object indicates the next hop of an LSP. The value of this object can be any valid IP address. This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSRedirectLSPSecondary.name: hwCBQoSRedirectLSPSecondary
hwCBQoSRedirectLSPSecondary.description: The value of this object identifies whether a primary or a standby LSP is used. The value can be main-lsp-path(1) or backup-lsp-path(2). The default value is main-lsp-path(1).

hwCBQoSMirrorCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSMirrorCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSMirrorCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Mirror configuration information.

hwCBQoSMirrorRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSMirrorRowStatus
hwCBQoSMirrorRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hwCBQoSUrpfCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSUrpfCfgInfoTable
hwCBQoSUrpfCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Urpf configuration information.

hwCBQoSUrpfCtrlType.name: hwCBQoSUrpfCtrlType
hwCBQoSUrpfCtrlType.description: The value of this object identifies URPF control type. The value can be strict(1) or loose(2). This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSUrpfAllowDefault.name: hwCBQoSUrpfAllowDefault
hwCBQoSUrpfAllowDefault.description: The value of this object identifies whether URPF flags the default route. The value can be 0 or 1. 0: indicates that the default route is not allowed. 1: indicates that the default route is allowed. The default value is 1.

hwCBQoSUrpfRowStatus.name: hwCBQoSUrpfRowStatus
hwCBQoSUrpfRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status. The value of this object can be Active(1), CreateAndGo(4), or Destroy(6). This object has no default value.

hwCBQoSCountCfgInfoTable.name: hwCBQoSCountCfgInfoTable
